## 12. FP8 All-Gather

FP8 all-gather is an FSDP2-only feature. Instead of all-gathering parameters in bfloat16
(2 bytes/value), FSDP2 can cast to FP8 (1 byte/value) before the collective, halving
all-gather communication volume.

### Requirements

- PyTorch 2.1+
- TorchAO (`pip install torchao`)
- NVIDIA Hopper GPUs (H100/H200) for native FP8 tensor core support

### Configuration

```python
plugin = FullyShardedDataParallelPlugin(
    fsdp_version=2,
    enable_fsdp_float8_all_gather=True,
    # Optional: only apply FP8 all-gather to specific layer types
    # Default filter is accelerate.utils.ao.filter_linear_layers
    # which applies FP8 only to nn.Linear layers
    filter_layer_for_fsdp_float8_all_gather=my_custom_filter,
)
```

### What the Default Filter Does

`accelerate.utils.ao.filter_linear_layers(module, layer_name)` returns `True` for
`nn.Linear` modules and `False` for everything else. This means:

- `nn.Linear` layers (attention projections, MLP layers): FP8 all-gather
- `nn.Embedding` layers: BF16 all-gather (embedding tables benefit from precision)
- `nn.LayerNorm`, `nn.RMSNorm`: BF16 all-gather (normalization params are small)

### When FP8 Helps

FP8 all-gather is beneficial when inter-GPU communication is the bottleneck (i.e., when
GPU compute finishes faster than the all-gather). On PCIe-connected GPUs or multi-node
setups with limited bandwidth, FP8 all-gather can measurably increase throughput.
On NVLink-only intra-node setups where NVLink bandwidth exceeds compute throughput, the
benefit is smaller but still present.

